385. salis Ausonii, ‘ the Italian sea ', unusual expression for the mare inferum, between Sicily and Latium.

386. lacus, the lake of Avernus near Vesuvius, and the other vol- canic lakes about, were supposed to be specially connected with the nether regions. The sulphureous stench, the earthquakes near, the cavernous ground, all helped these beliefs. See VI. 118.

Circae. Vergil identifies Circeii, promontory (originally an island) of the Latian coast, with Homer's ‘Aeaean island' dwelling of the enchantress Circe. See VIII. 11.
